# OpenForge — Web UI (always follow)

Git root is **`web/`**; SvelteKit lives in **`app/`**. Full reference: `docs/ui-ux/ui-engineering-web.md` and `docs/openforge-DL-1.0.md`.

## Theme

- Use **semantic Tailwind tokens** from `app/src/app.css` only: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `primary`, `destructive`, `muted-foreground`, etc.
- **No** ad-hoc hex or palette utilities (`bg-zinc-500`, random `oklch(...)`) in feature code. New colours → add CSS variables + `@theme` in `app/src/app.css`, then use utilities.
- **OpenForge data semantics** (profile timeline, request states, review severity): use **existing** `--color-data-*` / `--color-state-*` tokens or **Badge variants** in `app/src/lib/components/ui/badge/badge.svelte` — never duplicate badge/timeline styling on pages.

## Components

- **shadcn-svelte first**: add primitives with `cd app && npx shadcn-svelte@latest add <name> -y`. Implementations live in `app/src/lib/components/ui/`.
- **`ui/`** = registry components only. **`shell/`** = app chrome composed from `ui/` + Tailwind. Do not add parallel primitives (e.g. a second `Button` wrapper) unless this rule file is updated.
- **Reuse** by composing `ui/*` in routes/shell; extract shared layout only when multiple call sites need it.

## Design language

- Follow **DL-1.0** terminology (Request, Contributor, Reviewer, …) and **accessibility** (visible focus, labels, keyboard). Do not strip shadcn focus/ARIA patterns.
- **Do not rely on colour alone** for meaning (DL §6–§7); pair timeline/state with text or structure.

## Docs

- After materially changing tokens or UI rules, update `docs/ui-ux/ui-engineering-web.md` and/or `docs/ui-ux/theming.md` in the same change when practical.
